PackIt - Copyright Tab
#fH2:Copyright Tab
#Parent !Root

This screen contains the licence field from the control record and the text of the copyright record.

{fH4}Field{f}	{fH4}Description{f}
#Line
{*}Licence{*}	This is the licence the package is released under. It can be Free or Non Free. Free is defined as a package that meets the Open Source definition available at <http://www.opensource.org/docs/osd=>#URL http://www.opensource.org/docs/osd>.

	Common licences that are classified as free include:

#Indent +1
	è Apache License, 2.0
	è New and Simplified BSD licenses
	è Boost Software License (BSL1.0)
	è European Union Public License
	è GNU General Public License (GPL)
	è GNU General Public License version 3.0 (GPLv3)
	è GNU Library or "Lesser" General Public License (LGPL)
	è GNU Library or "Lesser" General Public License version 3.0 (LGPLv3)
	è MIT license
	è Mozilla Public License 1.1 (MPL)
	è zlib/libpng license
#Indent

	A Full list of currently approved free licences can be found at <http://www.opensource.org/licenses=>#URL http://www.opensource.org/licenses>.

{*}Copyright{*}	The copyright text for the package. This is required. It must contain the following information:

#Indent +1
	è the name of the upstream author(s)
	è the names of current and past package maintainers
	è the provenance of the upstream sources
	è a verbatim copy of the copyright notice and distribution licence
#indent

